properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 2 at 2:00PM MST until February 3 at 6:00PM MST by NWS Albuquerque NM
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected.

* WHERE...West Central Plateau, West Central Mountains, South
Central Highlands, Upper Tularosa Valley, Eastern Lincoln
County, Southwest Chaves County and San Agustin Plains and
Adjacent Lowlands.

* WHEN...From 10 AM to 6 PM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Remember to secure lightweight outdoor furniture.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong cross winds are expected along
Interstate 40 between Gallup and Grants. High profile vehicles
should use caution.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 6 PM MST MONDAY
